title.narrative: 101/001 By 2020, the quality of integrated service delivery and effective coverage have been strengthened in national and subnational health systems to support the well-being of children under 5 years and their mothers, including those infected and affected by HIV, in emergency and non-emergency situations, including urban.

description.narrative: The health system was strengthened through finalization of the maternal health strategy, newborn health implementation plan, urban immunization strategy, and strategy for WASH in Health facilities. As a result, 69,086 newborns were treated in SCANUs, 1,295 LBW babies received KMC, 3,101,446 children under two were fully immunized, and 215 maternal and 1,040 neonatal deaths were notified through MPDSR. In the Rohingya camps, 30,869 children were immunized, 16 healthcare facilities were supported with 141,910 children's consultations and 648 deliveries with essential Post Natal Care. A total of 62,000 women accessed HIV-testing and counselling and all HIV-positive pregnant women received PMTCT. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
